KxBGd"><span class="yCeTE">I loved it despite the mosquitoes.<br>I was there by 5.45am thinking they open at 6am but they open at only 7am in the winter <br>So I tried my luck along the road by the river outside and was very happy with more than 10 varieties including my ever sighting of a Rufous Treepie among others <br><br>I connected with 3 other bird watchers as we entered and enjoyed my sightings . I am still processing the pictures but there were several first timers for me.<br><br>Despite it being a thick forest if one has patience to stay still and ignore the mosquitoes, the chances of spotting become higher.<br><br>I wish they would open at 6 since I saw many flocks fly away between 6 and 7.<br><br>Affordable price. There are toilets inside. However own can see some plastic pollution as well as noise when young groups come in. href="/ShowUserReviews-g304558-d12282731-r780530696-Mousuni_Island-Kolkata_Calcutta_Kolkata_District_West_Bengal.html" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt ukgoS"><span class="yCeTE">A Weekend Getaway</span></a></div><div class="_T FKffI bmUTE"><div class="fIrGe _T bgMZj" style="-webkit-line-clamp:7;line-break:normal;cursor:pointer"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB KxBGd"><span class="yCeTE">Away from the city humdrum and the stress that our regular lives entail, Mousuni Island probably makes for an ideal place for a day or two in the seashore. The journey to reach this place  is painstaking , as it entails two to three different modes. one will be required to drive up to "Hujjater Ghat" in "Saat Mile" and from there cross the river in a boat or ferry; and then avail "toto" to reach the  resort. The place is chalked full of luxurious Resorts for a comfortable stay and among them ANANDADHARA PROJECT deserves a special mention , for their hospitality and quality food all within a pocket-friendly budget. Although the beach is not clean, but the sunset here is a spectacle; and  the evening is also well served with the delicious "barbecue" . In the day , one can also pay a visit to the adjacent village where fishermen and their wives live in harmony. The place is recommended mostly for people in groups of more than three.</span></div></div><div class="lszDU"><button class="UikNM _G B- _S _T c G_ P0 wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span><div class="CECjK"><svg viewBox="0 0 25 24" width="20px" height="20px" class="d Vb UmNoP"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M5.188 7.521l6.836 6.837 6.837-6.837 1.06 1.06-7.366 7.368a.75.75 0 01-1.061 0L4.127 8.582l1.06-1.06z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div></div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB xUqsL mowmC KxBGd"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/Attraction_Review-g304558-d12282731-Reviews-Mousuni_Island-Kolkata_Calcutta_Kolkata_District_West_Bengal.html#REVIEWS" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE">Review of: Mousuni Island</a></div><div class="TreSq"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written 4 January 2021</div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC.
